2021
May
SnowGlobe, a project started in my undergrad, was featured in an article by the NU Library. We also had a workshop for SnowGlobe which drew participants from over a hundred universities!
January
I joined Dr. Nayoun Kim for a workshop on experimental syntax held at Sungkyunkwan University (Korea). I helped design materials for a session on scripting online experiments with IBEX, including interactive slides made with R!
2020
November
I joined designer Will Chase on his stream to talk about the psycholinguistics of speech production for a data viz project on Michael’s speech errors in The Office. It was a very cool and unique opportunity to bring my two interests together!
October
My tutorial on stat_*() functions in {ggplot2} was featured as a highlight on the rweekly podcast, which curates weekly updates from the R community.
I became a data science tutor at MindCORE to help researchers at Penn with data visualization and R programming.
September
I have moved to Philadelphia to start my PhD in Linguistics at the University of Pennsylvania!
I presented a poster at AMLaP on my undergrad thesis research with my advisors Jennifer Cole and Masaya Yoshida.
June
I graduated from Northwestern University with a B.A. in Linguistics! I was also elected into Phi Beta Kappa and appointed as the Senior Marshal for Linguistics.

